    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1191" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀ - πήμων</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ονος</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πῆμα</span>):
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">without harm;</span> pass., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀπήμων
            ἦλθε, ἀπήμονα πέμπειν τινά</span>, ‘safe and sound,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 4.487</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od.
            13.39</span></i>; act., of anything that tends to safety, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">νόστος ἀπήμων</span>, ‘happy’ return, <i><span class="en">Od. 4.519</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; πομποί</span>, ‘kindly,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 8.566</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; οὖρος, ὕπνος</span>, etc. The distinction
          of act. and pass. is rather apparent than real.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
